  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare the less invasive Oesophageal Doppler cardiac output Monitor (ODM) to the invasive
      (standard of care) Transpulmonary Thermodilution cardiac output monitor (TPTD) in children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a validation study. The study period starts as soon as CMO approval is acquired and
      will end after inclusion of 17 patients. This study is designed to test the effectiveness of
      a non invasive ODM catheter compared to the invasive, gold standard, TPTD technique.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
